{{nihongo|'''Dōmo arigatō'''|どうもありがとう|}} is a [[Japanese language|Japanese]] expression that translates to "Thank you." Knowledge of the expression was popularized in the [[Western world]] at least in part by the song "[[Mr. Roboto]]" by [[Styx (band)|Styx]] which features the line "''Dōmo arigatō'', Mr. Roboto."

The line has been used as a pop culture reference a number of times, including in the films ''[[Austin Powers in Goldmember]]'', ''[[Tom Green: Subway Monkey Hour]]'', ''[[Kill Bill: Volume II]]'' and ''[[Dodgeball: A True Underdog Story]]'', the songs "The King of Bedside Manor" by the [[Barenaked Ladies]] and "This Could Have Been a Dance Revolution; But Now It's Just a Dance" by Rory, cartoons ''[[Futurama]]'', ''[[The Simpsons]]'' and [[My Life as a Teenage Robot]]. It is also used in Scrubs (Turk: "Gimme your pudding! Dōmo arigatō!").


